From 45656a900a24eeffc15ff813b72b21653ea1b9a4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zimuzo Ezeozue <zezeozue@google.com>
Date: Sat, 30 May 2026 14:40:16 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?soong:=20resident=20warm-incremental=20build=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=80=94=20O(edit)=20ninja=20generation=20+=20warm=20add?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Resident soong_build server (SOONG_PERSISTENT_REUSE_GRAPH=true) keeping the
resolved+mutated graph and caches in RAM across builds, with changed-file-only
reparse and the warm add/remove wiring. A warm edit reparses only the changed
.bp files, re-mutates only the affected closure, regenerates only dirty modules,
and delta-writes only the shards that changed.

Measured on real AOSP (aosp_cf_x86_64_phone-trunk_staging-userdebug), all
byte-identical to a cold rebuild (cmp, 403/403 shards):
  - property edit (services.core.unboosted): analysis 131s -> 4.4s
  - add a module: warm, 1 of 50 shards rewritten, ~34s wall (was a crash/fallback)
  - remove a module: falls back to a correct full rebuild (name interface has no
    ModuleRemover; next step)

Includes: BeginIncrementalBuild before DiffParsedModules (nil-map crash fix);
changed-file-only reparse with full-reparse fallback; add/remove routed through
IncrementalAddModules/Remove with fallback. Local/experimental.

Change-Id: Id5fffb376513e3028b76af007f85b687bd351126
